  "author_association": "NONE",
  "body": "Our security scanner is detecting that backup directories created by fluentd are world writable.\r\nI think they are getting created [here](https://github.com/fluent/fluentd/blob/master/lib/fluent/plugin/output.rb#L1206): \r\n\r\n```ruby\r\n          FileUtils.mkdir_p(backup_dir) unless Dir.exist?(backup_dir)\r\n          File.open(backup_file, 'ab', system_config.file_permission || 0644) { |f|\r\n            chunk.write_to(f)\r\n          }\r\n```\r\nIs there any reason why those directories need to be world writable, rather than set to 755?\r\n\r\nWe are using fluentd version 1.7.0\r\n\r\n\r\n",
